output.title: Cheesy Vegetable Frittata
output.description: A vibrant and hearty vegetarian frittata featuring fluffy eggs, melted cheese, and a colorful medley of fresh tomatoes, onions, and bell peppers. It's a versatile dish, perfect for any meal of the day.
ingredients: 1/2 cup shredded cheddar cheese (or mozzarella, or a blend)
Freshly ground black pepper to taste
Fresh parsley or chives, chopped (for garnish, optional)
instructions: Heat olive oil in an oven-safe, non-stick skillet (about 10-inch) over medium heat. Add the chopped onion and bell pepper and cook until softened, about 5-7 minutes.
Add the diced tomato to the skillet and cook for another 2-3 minutes, just until slightly softened. Remove the skillet from heat temporarily.
In a large bowl, whisk the eggs with milk or cream (if using), salt, and black pepper until well combined and slightly frothy.
Stir half of the shredded cheese into the egg mixture.
Pour the egg mixture evenly over the cooked vegetables in the skillet. Sprinkle the remaining half of the cheese over the top.
Return the skillet to the stovetop over medium-low heat for about 3-5 minutes, allowing the edges to set without browning too much.
Transfer the skillet to the preheated oven and bake for 15-20 minutes, or until the frittata is set in the center and lightly golden on top.
Remove from oven and let it rest for 5 minutes before slicing and serving. Garnish with fresh parsley or chives if desired.

reference.title: Hearty Vegetarian Scramble with Cheese
reference.description: A quick and delicious vegetarian scramble packed with colorful vegetables and melted cheese, perfect for a satisfying breakfast, brunch, or light meal.
ingredients: 1 cup shredded cheese (cheddar, mozzarella, or your favorite blend)
Salt and freshly ground black pepper to taste
Fresh parsley or chives, chopped (for garnish, optional)
instructions: In a medium bowl, whisk together eggs, milk (if using), salt, and pepper until well combined.
Heat olive oil or butter in a non-stick skillet over medium heat. Add chopped onion and bell pepper and sauté for 5-7 minutes, until softened.
Add diced tomato to the skillet and cook for another 2-3 minutes, stirring occasionally, until slightly softened.
Pour the egg mixture into the skillet with the vegetables. Let it sit undisturbed for about 30 seconds until the edges begin to set.

Using a spatula, gently push the cooked egg from the edges towards the center, allowing the uncooked egg to flow underneath. Continue this process, stirring and scrambling gently, until the eggs are mostly set but still slightly moist.
Sprinkle the shredded cheese over the eggs. Cook for another 1-2 minutes, stirring gently, until the cheese is melted and incorporated.
Remove from heat. Garnish with fresh parsley or chives, if desired. Serve hot with your favorite toast or side dishes.
